data.enText: the parts of sth that are left after the other parts have been used, eaten, removed, etc.

data.chText: 她把剩下的午饭喂狗了。
data.enText: She fed the remains of her lunch to the dog.

data.chText: 古代遗物；古迹；遗迹；遗址
data.enText: the parts of ancient objects and buildings that have survived and are discovered in the present day
the remains of a Roman fort
the body of a dead person or animal

ex.chText: 她退休余下的时间都在养花中度过。
ex.enText: She spent the remainder of her retirement growing flowers.
When will the remainder be paid off?
Twenty-eight divided by nine gives you a remainder of 1.

synonyms.bx: 泛指从整体取走或用掉部分后的剩余部分，通常与定冠词 the 连用；也指除法运算中的余数。

ex.chText: 她把晚饭的剩菜扔掉了。
ex.enText: She threw away the remains of her supper.

ex.chText: 几处古罗马遗迹得到了很好的保护。
ex.enText: Several Roman remains have been well protected.

synonyms.bx: 指某物得以保留且未被破坏的部分。

ex.chText: 我们两人每人只能拿两个包，剩下的怎么办？
ex.enText: Each of us can only carry two bags. What about the rest?

ex.chText: 3名银行劫匪被捕，其余的逃走了。
ex.enText: Three of the bank robbers were arrested, and the rest escaped.

ex.chText: 你可以把剩下的西瓜带回宿舍。
ex.enText: You can bring the rest of this watermelon to your dormitory.

ex.chText: 他希望他能在一个安静的村庄里度过余生。
ex.enText: He wished that he could spend the rest of his life in a quiet village.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，通常与定冠词 the 连用。

d: 剩余部分；余下的人（或物）

ex.chText: 是什么造成了原油过剩？
ex.enText: What causes the surplus of crude oil?

ex.chText: 被剪掉的多余部分可以做什么用？
ex.enText: What can we do with the surplus trimmed away?

synonyms.bx: 指超出需求的过剩数量。

tr: the dead body of a human being
example: the cadaver was intended for dissection
the end of the police search was the discovery of a corpse
the murderer confessed that he threw the stiff in the river
honor comes to bless the turf that wraps their clay

tr: any object that is left unused or still extant
example: I threw out the remains of my dinner

value.def: If someone or something remains in a particular state or condition, they stay in that state or condition and do not change.

example.ex: The three men remained silent...
example.tran: 这3个人保持着沉默。

example.ex: The situation remains tense...
example.tran: 形势持续紧张。

example.ex: The government remained in control...
example.tran: 政府仍控制着局势。

example.ex: He remained a formidable opponent...
example.tran: 他依然是一个令人敬畏的对手。

example.ex: It remains possible that bad weather could tear more holes in the tanker's hull.
example.tran: 恶劣天气仍然可能使油轮船体遭受更多破损。

value.def: If you remain in a place, you stay there and do not move away.

example.ex: He will have to remain in hospital for at least 10 days...
example.tran: 他至少得在医院里呆10天。

example.ex: From time to time, James remained at home with his family.
example.tran: 詹姆斯偶尔留在家里陪家人。

value.def: You can say that something remains when it still exists.

example.ex: Many of the differences in everyday life remain...
example.tran: 日常生活中的许多差异仍然存在。

example.ex: The wider problem remains...
example.tran: 更普遍的问题仍未解决。

example.ex: There remains deep mistrust of his government.
example.tran: 仍然有人对他领导的政府很不信任。

value.def: If something remains to be done, it has not yet been done and still needs to be done.

example.ex: Major questions remain to be answered about his work...
example.tran: 关于他工作的许多重要问题仍然悬而未决。

example.ex: Huge amounts of weapons remain to be collected.
example.tran: 大量的武器仍有待收缴。

value.def: The remains of something are the parts of it that are left after most of it has been taken away or destroyed.

example.ex: They were tidying up the remains of their picnic.
example.tran: 他们正在收拾野餐后剩下的东西。

example.ex: ...the charred remains of a tank.
example.tran: 烧焦的坦克残骸

example.ex: ...the remains of an ancient mosque.
example.tran: 一座古清真寺的遗迹

value.def: The remains of a person or animal are the parts of their body that are left after they have died, sometimes after they have been dead for a long time.

example.ex: The unrecognizable remains of a man had been found...
example.tran: 一具无法辨认的男性尸体被发现了。

example.ex: More human remains have been unearthed in the north of the country.
example.tran: 在该国北部挖出了更多的人类遗骨。

value.def: Historical remains are things that have been found from an earlier period of history, usually buried in the ground, for example parts of buildings and pieces of pottery.

example.ex: There are Roman remains all around us.
example.tran: 我们周围都是古罗马的遗迹。

value.def: You can use remain in expressions such as the fact remains that or the question remains whether to introduce and emphasize something that you want to talk about.

example.ex: The fact remains that inflation is unacceptably high...
example.tran: 事实是通货膨胀率仍高得离谱。

example.ex: The question remains whether he was fully aware of the claims.
example.tran: 问题是他是否完全意识到了这些要求。

value.tran: （事实、问题等)仍然是(表示强调)

value.def: If you say that it remains to be seen whether something will happen, you mean that nobody knows whether it will happen.

example.ex: It remains to be seen whether her parliamentary colleagues will agree.
example.tran: 她的国会同僚是否同意，现在还无从知晓。
